<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">

 <head>

  <title>CSS Test: Casdading order - sort by order specified</title>

  <link rel="author" title="GÃ©rard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/" />
  <link rel="help" title="6.4.1 Cascading order" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/cascade.html#cascading-order" />
  <link rel="match" href="reference/sort-by-order-001-ref.xht" />

  <meta content="" name="flags" />
  <meta content="If 2 declarations have the same media, the same importance (normal or !important), the same origin (author, user or user agent) and the same specificity, then the latter specified wins." name="assert" />

  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
  div#hgroup > h1  /* a=0 b=1 c=0 d=2 -> specificity = 0,1,0,2 */
  {
  background-color: red;
  color: white;
  }
  
  div > h1#heading /* a=0 b=1 c=0 d=2 -> specificity = 0,1,0,2 */ 
  {
  background-color: green;
  color: white;
  }
  ]]></style>

 </head>

 <body>

  <p>Test passes if the sentence has a green background and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>

  <div id="hgroup">
    <h1 id="heading">This sentence should have a green background.</h1>
  </div>

 </body>
</html>